UNC-Asheville, Clemson Win Opening Games of NCAA Basketball Tournament

-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 
2011-03-16T04:38:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-16/unc-asheville-clemson-win-opening-games-of-ncaa-basketball-tournament.html
The University of North Carolina-
Asheville and Clemson University won the first two games of
college basketball’s national men’s championship.  No. 16 UNC-Asheville beat the University of Arkansas-
Little Rock 81-77 in overtime and Clemson defeated University of
Alabama-Birmingham 70-52 at the National Collegiate Athletic
Association tournament.  The remaining two play-in games are scheduled for today,
with full tournament play beginning March 17 at eight sites. The
field was expanded to 68 teams this year.  UNC-Asheville will next play Southeast Regional top seed
Pittsburgh, while No. 12 Clemson will play  West Virginia , the
fifth seed in the East. Both games are tomorrow.  The UNC-Asheville Bulldogs (20-13) were led by Matt Dickey
and J.P. Primm with 22 points each at the University of Dayton
Arena in Dayton,  Ohio .  In the second game at the same venue, Jerai Grant had 22
points for the Clemson Tigers (22-11), who had a 39-27 halftime
lead.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nancy Kercheval in Washington at 
 nkercheval@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael Sillup at 
 msillup@bloomberg.net  